eNCA's Silindelo Masikane reports. Courtesy of #DStv403 KIMBERLEY - "Devastating" is how Basic Education Minister Angie Motshekga has described the possibility of schools not reopening on 19 July. Motshekga has been monitoring the rollout of vaccinations in the education sector, now in its second week. READ: Teachers to be vaccinated from 23 June until schools close Motshekga said it is imperative that schools reopen on 19 July, but only if it's safe to do so. READ: Free State pushing hard to vaccinate teachers Motshekga's next stop will be the Eastern Cape. The department remains confident it will meet its target of inoculating 582,000 personnel by 8 July. Watch the video above for more details on this story.